cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "TTE_CC: Claude Code skills for Target Trial Emulation"
message: "If you use this toolkit, please cite it and the methodological sources below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Jacob
    family-names: Jameson
    affiliation: Harvard University
repository-code: "https://github.com/jacobjameson/TTE_CC"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - causal inference
  - target trial emulation
  - observational data
  - Claude Code
abstract: >
  TTE_CC is a set of Claude Code skills and course-faithful R helpers for
  performing target trial emulation in the style taught by the Harvard CAUSALab
  Target Trial Emulation course. It is an independent, unaffiliated toolkit that
  operationalizes the published target-trial-emulation framework; it does not
  redistribute any course materials or data.
references:
  - type: book
    title: "Causal Inference: What If"
    authors:
      - given-names: Miguel A.
        family-names: Hernán
      - given-names: James M.
        family-names: Robins
    year: 2020
    publisher:
      name: "Chapman & Hall/CRC"
    url: "https://www.hsph.harvard.edu/miguel-hernan/causal-inference-book/"
  - type: article
    title: "Using Big Data to Emulate a Target Trial When a Randomized Trial Is Not Available"
    authors:
      - given-names: Miguel A.
        family-names: Hernán
      - given-names: James M.
        family-names: Robins
    journal: "American Journal of Epidemiology"
    year: 2016
    volume: 183
    issue: 8
    start: 758
    end: 764
    doi: "10.1093/aje/kwv254"
